      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here are the full bibliographic details for Shannon's landmark paper:\n\n**Citation:**\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Shannon, C.E. (1948), \"A Mathematical Theory of Communication,\" *Bell System Technical Journal*, Volume 27, Issue 3, July 1948, Pages 379–423."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\nThe paper was actually published across two issues of the journal: "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "pp. 379–423 in *Bell System Technical Journal*, Vol. 27, No. 3, July 1948, and pp. 623–656 in No. 4, October 1948."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n**Additional details:**\n\n- **DOI:** https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1538-7305.1948.tb01338.x\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "It is an article by mathematician Claude Shannon published in the *Bell System Technical Journal* in 1948."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "It has tens of thousands of citations, being one of the most influential and cited scientific papers of all time, as it gave rise to the field of information theory."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "It was renamed *The Mathematical Theory of Communication* in the 1949 book of the same name, a small but significant title change after realizing the generality of this work."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "On the first page of the paper is the first appearance of the term \"bit\" for \"binary digit.\""
